Introduction
\layout Standard

In this exercise you will make a theoretical investigation of the electric
 field associated with the atomic nucleus.
 Our current understanding of the nucleus is the product of scattering experimen
ts where a projectile (e.g.
 an electron, photon, or even another nucleus) is given an initial kinetic
 energy and collides with a target nucleus (see figure below).
 
